# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# WHAT IS yuin/goldmark AND WHY IS IT THE 74TH Go CLI LIBRARY?
#
# yuin/goldmark is the recommended Go Markdown library since
# 2020 when Hugo (the largest Go-based static site generator)
# migrated from blackfriday to goldmark.  Distinct from Go's
# stdlib (no Markdown support) and from earlier alternatives
# (russross/blackfriday — partially CommonMark, gomarkdown/
# markdown — fork of blackfriday).
#
# Five distinguishing characteristics from pulldown-cmark
# (R665):
#
#   1. AST VS EVENT — goldmark builds a full AST; pulldown-
#      cmark emits events.  AST enables random-access
#      transformations (e.g., link rewriting, footnote
#      renumbering, TOC extraction) at the cost of memory.
#      Pull events are streaming-friendly + memory-efficient
#      but harder to inspect the document structurally.
#
#   2. EXTENDER INTERFACE — goldmark extensions implement
#      Extender; each extension can register parsers + inline
#      parsers + renderers + transformers.  Built-in
#      extensions: Table, Strikethrough, TaskList, Linkify,
#      DefinitionList, Footnote, Typographer, GFM (combined).
#      Third-party: highlight (Chroma), mathjax, mermaid,
#      wikilinks, etc.  Pulldown-cmark requires forking +
#      patching for new features.
#
#   3. AST.WALK VISITOR PATTERN — `ast.Walk(root, walker)`
#      traverses the document with entering/leaving callbacks.
#      Pulldown-cmark has no equivalent — caller manually
#      iterates the event stream.
#
#   4. HTML SAFE BY DEFAULT — raw HTML escaped unless
#      WithUnsafe() opt-in.  Pulldown-cmark: equivalent via
#      Options::ENABLE_SAFE_LINKS / HTML escaping mode.
#
#   5. YUIN ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — Yusuke Inuzuka maintains
#      goldmark + goldmark-meta + goldmark-highlighting +
#      gopher-lua + gluamapper.  Distinct from Raph Levien
#      (pulldown-cmark / graphics engineering), and from
#      other Go maintainers (Steve Francia, Mathew Roy,
#      fsnotify org).
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# THE stitchmd CLI — Go stdlib `flag` + goldmark + markdownfmt
#
# stitchmd's CLI is in flags.go.  Uses Go's stdlib `flag` package
# (not cobra / urfave/cli) for minimal binary size.
#
# Source:
#     flag := flag.NewFlagSet("stitchmd", flag.ContinueOnError)
#     flag.StringVar(&opts.Preface, "preface", "", "")
#     flag.StringVar(&opts.Output, "o", "", "")
#     flag.StringVar(&opts.Dir, "C", "", "")
#     flag.IntVar(&opts.Offset, "offset", 0, "")
#     flag.BoolVar(&opts.NoTOC, "no-toc", false, "")
#     flag.Var(&opts.ColorOutput, "color", "")
#     flag.BoolVar(&opts.Diff, "d", false, "")
#     flag.BoolVar(&opts.Diff, "diff", false, "")
#     flag.BoolVar(&opts.Unsafe, "unsafe", false, "")
#     flag.BoolVar(&p.version, "version", false, "")
#     flag.BoolVar(&p.help, "help", false, "")
#     flag.BoolVar(&p.help, "h", false, "")
#
# Flags (Go stdlib flag uses single dash):
#   -offset N           heading level offset (positive deeper,
#                       negative shallower)
#   -no-toc             do not generate table of contents
#                       under each section
#   -preface FILE       insert FILE verbatim at top of output
#   -o FILE             write output to FILE (default stdout;
#                       use '-' for stdout)
#   -C DIR              change to DIR before reading files
#                       (default: directory of FILE)
#   -d, -diff           report diff to stdout instead of
#                       writing file (requires -o)
#   -color MODE         color mode: always | never | auto
#                       (default auto)
#   -unsafe             allow file references outside working
#                       directory
#   -version            print version
#   -h, -help           show help
#
# Positional:
#   FILE                input file (use '-' for stdin)
#
# goldmark is used internally for parsing the input Markdown
# summary file + the inlined target files; markdownfmt v3 is
# used for canonical re-rendering of the combined output.
#
# Five-axis distinctness from pulldown-cmark (R665):
#
#   1. AST VS EVENT — full document tree vs streaming events.
#
#   2. EXTENDER INTERFACE — first-class extension architecture.
#
#   3. AST.WALK VISITOR — random-access traversal.
#
#   4. PURE GO — no Cgo, no C toolchain.
#
#   5. YUIN ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — Japanese Go maintainer.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# COMMAND-LINE OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/abhinav/stitchmd/blob/main/flags.go
# https://github.com/abhinav/stitchmd/blob/main/usage.txt
# Go stdlib flag.FlagSet definitions.)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

local -a _stitchmd_color
_stitchmd_color=(
    'always:always color output'
    'never:never color output'
    'auto:auto-detect color (default)'
)

_arguments -s -S \
    '-offset+[heading level offset (positive deeper, negative shallower)]:offset:_default' \
    '-no-toc[do not generate table of contents under each section]' \
    '-preface+[insert FILE verbatim at top of output]:file:_files' \
    '-o+[write output to FILE (use - for stdout)]:file:_files' \
    '-C+[change to DIR before reading files]:directory:_files -/' \
    '(-d -diff)'{-d,-diff}'[report diff to stdout instead of writing file (requires -o)]' \
    '-color+[color mode]:mode:->color' \
    '-unsafe[allow file references outside working directory]' \
    '-version[print version]' \
    '(- *)'{-h,-help}'[show help]' \
    '*:input file:_files -g "*.md"' \
    && ret=0

case $state in
    color)
        _describe -t modes 'color mode' _stitchmd_color && ret=0
        ;;
esac

return ret
